            <h1 class=" fw-bold lh-1 text-center">Operations</h1>
            <br>
            <p class=" lead "> 
I am responsible for the strategic development, planning, organisation and delivery of the pharmacy patient service areas across all UCLH hospital sites and the Pharmacy Distribution Center. At the core of this responsibility lies the Medicines Supply chain process (from receipt of medicine to supply to our service users). <br>Our service users are composed of patients, hospital ward areas, other NHS trusts, clinical research facilities, external sales customers, commissionaires and homecare companies. <br>
I look after two disctinct areas:<br>
a. Patient services:  I am responsible for the safe and efficient delivery of pharmacy services to patients in line with professional, regulatory and legal requirements within the dispensary areas. In and outpatient dispensing services are provided from five dispensary areas servicing seven hospital sites. Our dispensaries complete approx 30,000 transactions/lines per month. <br>
b.Pharmacy Distribution Center: Purchases in excess of £110m of medicines per year and is licensed by the MHRA as a medicines wholesaler and by the Home Office to supply Controlled Drugs. In addition to the provision of medicines to all hospital areas, the unit provides services to a number of external customers, including other local NHS trusts. 
 </p>
